🧬 Full auto‑detect logic block (clean version)
ini
# HDMI EDID negotiation
hdmi_mode = HDMI.get_preferred_mode();   # e.g., 1280x720

# Compute 4x3 viewport
screen_w = hdmi_mode.width;
screen_h = hdmi_mode.height;

viewport_h = screen_h;
viewport_w = (screen_h * 4) / 3;

viewport_x = (screen_w - viewport_w) / 2;
viewport_y = 0;

# Render Nano64 framebuffer into viewport
nano.render_to_viewport(viewport_x, viewport_y, viewport_w, viewport_h);

# Fill outside with black
nano.clear_outside_viewport();
This is exactly how retro‑accurate HDMI output is done.
